    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/485</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-18T23:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 19, 5.03 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5110. Your 5598 to [via] London, September 13.<note n="1" xml:id="d407fn1">See
                        final paragraph of telegram No. 1337 to the Ambassador in Great Britain, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_249">p. 249</ref>.</note> In
                    presenting this matter to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PS1">Pichon</persName>,
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs, to-day, he told me that the French Government was
                    familiar with the distinguished service and ability of Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName>, knowing something of his work
                    at Harbin. The Minister stated that his Government was in entire accord with the
                    purpose of the American Government as set forth in its telegram; recognizing the
                    need of such an undertaking, it would likewise receive the cooperation of his
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
